heaviest_rainfall.status: Today's storm ranked 7th for total rainfall with 22.48mm having fallen, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  8.3mm per hour fell at points during the storm which lasted 28.2 hours.  The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm fell at a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour over the 144.8 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: On 02 September 2025, the rain fell at an exceptional rate, peaking at 34.3mm per hour, the heaviest downpour recorded.  A total of 21.19mm fell over the 15.0 hour storm.

longest_rain.status: A storm today ranked 8th for the longest continuous rainfall according to our records, lasting a total of28.2 hours.  It came with 22.48mm of rainfall, at times, falling at 8.3mm per hour.  Rain fell for 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 47.89mm with a maximum intensity of 24.6mm per hour.
